{
  "id": "aquinas-qd-de-anima",
  "name": {
    "en-US": "Disputed Question on the Soul",
    "la": "Quaestio Disputata de Anima"
  },
  "author": {
    "en-US": "St. Thomas Aquinas",
    "la": "Sanctus Thomas Aquinas"
  },
  "description": {
    "en-US": "A single disputed question of twenty-one articles on the human soul — its substantiality, its union with the body, its powers, and its survival after death. Distinct from Aquinas's commentary on Aristotle's *De anima*.",
    "la": "Quaestio disputata una vigintiunius articulorum, de anima humana — substantialitate, unione cum corpore, potentiis, et superstitione post mortem. Distincta a commentario in Aristotelis *De anima*."
  },
  "composed": "1265–1266",
